-- Elektra Tumbles 15% in Mexico City After Leaving MSCI
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-05-16T14:25:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-16/elektra-tumbles-15-in-mexico-city-after-leaving-msci-correct-.html
(Corrects date of announcement in second paragraph.)  Grupo Elektra SA, the retail and
banking company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas ,
plunged as much as 15 percent in Mexico City trading.  The stock was removed from  MSCI Inc. (MSCI) ’s family of indexes in
a rebalancing announced yesterday and effective May 31,
according to a statement on MSCI’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
